30/05/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- Four people were injured on Sunday (May 29th) in a clash between supporters of the Nationalist Movement Party (MHP) and the pro-Kurdish Peace and Democracy Party (BDP). 
The windows of nearby shops and cars were also broken. 
The incident happened in Istanbul's Kazlicesme district, several hours before a MHP rally linked to the June 12th general elections. 
(Dogan, Hurriyet - 29/05/11)
